<DESCRIPT>  MOVIE; RANKING; CHART  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  'NEW JACK CITY" continued to make news over the weekend -- not for violence at
movie theaters but for another strong showing at the box office, despite the
gangster film's limited release.;    With ticket sales of $5.8 million and a
strong per-screen average of $6,584, "New Jack City" finished in second place
behind "The Silence of the Lambs."  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  'NEW JACK' NOT LOUD ENOUGH TO SILENCE 'LAMBS'  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Film  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     "New Jack City" is playing on almost half as many screens as "The Silence
of the Lambs.";    "The Silence of the Lambs," starring Jodie Foster as an FBI
trainee in pursuit of a psychopathic killer-dressmaker, took first place for
the fifth consecutive week. It made $7.7 million over the weekend and has
pulled in $68.9 million to date.;    "New Jack City" was in second, and
"Sleeping With the Enemy," a thriller featuring Julia Roberts, claimed third,
with proceeds of $4.7 million.;    "Class Action," a new courtroom drama
pairing Gene Hackman and Mary Elizabeth Mastrantonio as father-daughter
lawyers on opposite sides of a case, landed in fourth on a gate of $4.2
million.;    In ninth, with receipts of $2.7 million, was "Home Alone." The
