<LEADPARA>  STEVEN Seagal's new action film "Out for Justice" debuted in the No. 1 box
office spot with weekend sales of $10.5 million, nearly double the take of
second place "Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles II.";    It was the best opening
for any movie starring the pony-tailed martial arts star. Last October, his
"Marked for Death" opened to $10.517 in business, just $7,000 less than "Out
for Justice's" weekend take of $10.524 million. In February, "Hard to Kill"
grossed $9.2 million.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  'OUT FOR JUSTICE' COMES IN AT NO. 1 IN ITS
FIRST WEEK OUT  </HEADLINE>
