"The Silence of the Lambs," casting Jodie Foster as an FBI trainee in pursuit
of a serial killer, has now made $100.1 million. It is the first 1991 release
to pass the $100 million mark.;    "Home Alone" is about to slip off the Top
10 charts after one of the most amazing runs in Hollywood history. In ninth
place for the weekend, "Home Alone" grossed $1.8 million and has earned $262.5
