<TEXT>
<P>
Negotiations are being completed for Arnold Schwarzenegger to star in Nelson 
Entertainment's "The Taking of Beverly Hills," a fall start locally, then 
moving on to Mexico City. The hostage thriller, written by Rick Natkin and 
David Fuller, is in the "Die Hard" mold, with Arnold as the muscular hero. 
Sidney Furie directs and David Giler produces. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Michelle Pfeiffer -- mentioned in the press as a possibility for the role of a 
female FBI agent investigating a series of grisly murders in Orion's "The 
Silence of the Lambs" -- has some competition, according to a production 
source. Discussions are also under way with Jodie Foster and Meg Ryan. The 
adaptation of Thomas Harris' best seller starts in late September with 
producer-director Jonathon Demme. Jack Nicholson is reportedly negotiating to 
play creepy Dr. Lektor, an institutionalized killer. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Nicolas Cage and Judge Reinhold team in October for Electric Pictures' "Adios 
Thierry," a taut romantic thriller. Marie Kornhauser's script centers on a 
woman, frustrated in marriage, who enters an affair with the best friend (Cage) 
of her husband (Reinhold). Reinhold co-produces with William Blaylock and Eyal 
Rimmon. Sam Pillsbury directs in New Orleans for ITC Productions. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Veteran actor Arthur Kennedy plays the title role in Frame by Frame 
Productions' "Grandpa," filming in Northern California next month. The story 
focuses on the strained relationship between Kennedy and grandson Lee Maddox. 
Nicole Eggert plays the young woman who smoothes their troubled waters. Alan 
Ruffier wrote the screenplay and directs for producer Tom Durbin. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Newcomer Balthazar Getty (son of John Paul III) stars as a young man on the 
rodeo circuit who tries to affect a rapprochement with his father in producer 
Martin Poll's "Home Grown." Ben Johnson, Tess Harper and Gary Busey co-star in 
Joel Don Humphrey's script, directed by Stuart Rosenberg. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Alexander Gudonov plays a modern Norseman in search of a priceless artifact in 
Hyperion's "Full Moon," a lighthearted thriller filming next month in Toronto. 
Writer-director Willard Carroll's screenplay centers on the mythical rune 
stone, a harbinger of disaster. Peter Riegert, Dennis Boutsikaris and William 
Hickey co-star for producer Joe Michael Terry. . . . Rain Pryor (daughter of 
Richard) joins the cast of Pressman Films' "Blackbird Fly" as the daughter in a 
strife-ridden black family. Danny Glover stars and co-produces the drama by 
writer-director Charles Burnett. . . . Virginia Madsen lures Don Johnson from a 
straight and narrow path in Orion's "Hot Spot." Dennis Hopper directs the 
steamy thriller, filming next month in Texas. LEONARD KLADY 
</P>
